This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a method for regularization and model selection that simultaneously learns both the model architecture and parameters. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on image classification datasets (CIFAR and Image Net), which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper uses back-propagation, which is a common technique in neural networks, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper's focus on learning shared image representations and hierarchical network structures suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
